That\'s not true at all.  The price of goods has always been based on a
few simple variables.  The type of world the goods are going to, the
type of world the goods were coming from, and the tech levels of each
respective world.

So, if the world that you\'re heading to is some TL14 technological
wonder, with computers coming from a TL15 world, but there is very
little agriculture, then rice coming in from a TL9 would actually be a
scarcer then the computers, thus the higher price for rice.  See, it\'s
all really simply economics, and supply and demand.

Also, in case anyone out there is wondering, a simple glance give me
the impression that the tables from MT and TNE are the same.  I could
be wrong about one or two little sections though (I didn\'t do a
thourough comparison).

