    'body' => '
   Just what does the Imperial Army do?  I have a fair idea of what the 
Imperial Marines do.
They serve as shipboard troop on Imperial Naval vessels.  They perform 
planetary invasions in a fashion similar to present day US Marine Amphibious 
Assault  Groups.   They provide security functions at Imperial Naval bases.  
Given what I know of the Imperial Military model, the Imperial Marines are 
probably under the control, or at least administration of, the Imperial Navy.
   The Imperial Army basic function is to control planetary surface.  As the 
old adage goes, You can fly over it, you can bomb it, but you really dont 
control it till you can stand a 19 year old kid with a rifle on it. The Navy 
performs surface bombardments.  The Marines perform assault landing to take 
control of the spaceport and planetary defenses.  Then the Army comes in to
capture the hearts and minds of the local population.   Failing that, the
Army 
tries to keep the number of bombing and sniper attacks down.
   Such a task takes a lot of troops.  Dont forget that for every trooper you

have carrying a rifle, you have five soldiers performing support tasks.  
Maintaining such an organization full time is a big task, even for the 
Imperium.  This is why I agree with the Steve on the structure of the
Imperial 
Army.  The actual full time, Imperial Army consists of a core of  Officers
and 
senior NCOs who serve as a Cadre core for member planet Armies called up for 
Imperial service.
   For example, after the 5th Frontier War, the Imperium has taken control of

several planets from the Sword World Confederation.  Rather than garrison
each 
planet with several regiments of TL14/15 Imperial Marines, Several Division
of
planetary army troops for each occupied planet are brought in from the
Marches
and placed under Imperial Army Command.   The troops get Imperial Army tags 
for their helmets and Imperial Army patches for their sleeves.  Overall
command and most staff positions would be filled by full time Imperial Army 
personnel.   Some of the captured worlds are only TL 6.  You dont need TL 15 
Marines for that.  A Division or two of TL 8 or 9 troop with TL C support 
units should do the trick.  You can further stack the deck with a light 
cruiser or two in orbit (You take the low road.  Ill take the High Road and 
rain Death all over ye.)
    Using this model the local planetary governments pays the bulk of the
cost
of maintaining the Army units.  The Imperial government would supply some 
funds.  Think of it as incentive to maintain the Army with Imperial standard 
equipment.  This way if you get two TL A divisions from two different
planets,
they use the same ammo, basically the same weapons and theyll be
able to read able to read and understand each others rank tabs.
    The Imperium would start picking up more of the tab once the units are 
called into Imperial service.  Then the logistics machine that makes up the 
bulk of the full time Imperial Army would swing into play.  Making sure the 
units go where theyre supposed to, providing full time Imperial Army cadre 
troops, providing the supply lines, that sort of thing.
    The Imperial Army would have large bases scattered around the Imperium. 
These bases would provide the administrative offices, training facilities and

storage.  Member planets would be required to send a certain percentage of 
their  officers to train at Imperial Army facilities.   
The Imperial Army would also provide specialized training for member planet 
units.  Most member worlds with a standing army would have a small Imperial 
Army detachment.  This Imperial Army unit would consist of mostly officers
and
a logistics staff (perhaps assigned by the local army).  Their task would to
assure Imperial standards in equipment and training are maintained and to 
coordinate local army units in the event of Imperial call up.


