    'from' => 'Anders Lindborg',
    'body' => 'It has been proposed that the breakdown of isotopes in the human body will
cause cancer in a high percentage of those who spend extreme periods of time
in a low berth. Apparently the body is only able to heal this damage at 
normal temperatures of operation. A simple solution to this could be the
assumption that all low berths are constructed to include a small but
serviceable nuclear damper, which effectively stops all nuclear breakdown
in it\'s limited area of effect. I feel this solution makes it possible
for the harried GM to ignore the whole issue and get on with playing the
game. :-) Say after me everyone: "This is only a game! We\'re supposed to
have fun! Nitpicking over the amount of realism in the game reduces the
fun in it!" All this is, of course, IMHO. Flames to my e-mail adress, not
to the list, please. *Thank you for reading this far!*
/Anders
