    'body' => 'Hi All,

Regarding the Syleans.....

Seth wrote:

>1.) Where/when did this happen? (I don\'t doubt you, I just don\'t seem to have
>    read the same sources.)

>2.) Possibly Sylean became the court language of the Imperium.

I was under the impression that the worlds of the Sylean Federation 
formed the beginnings of the Third Imperium. I believe that The 
Travellers Digest Number 18: A Concise History of the Third Imperium
gives a good quick summary of how the Sylean Federation rose out of
the Long Night mostly due to four different MegaCorps (LSP,
Zirunkariish, Tukera, and GSbAG).

It also mentions that Sylea had a TL12 Navy with meson screens giving it
a competitive advantage. The Sylean Federation Scout Service increased
the size of the Federation by recontacting other systems and trading 
technology for membership. 

As regards the court language I think that Survival Margin mentions
this Lucan incident. As a reaction to the Rebellion I think Lucan
changed it to Sylean. I don\'t have SM with me though, so its just a
distant memory.



TTFN

Glenn


