  {
    'body' => 'Hi, all...I was reading through the original MERCHANT PRINCE Book 7, and 
was reminded that at one time, GDW had available for sale a disk-based 
text program called TRADER.  It was written in DOS 3.3, requiring 48k and 
a single diskdrive.
  I know it\'s laughable these days, but my computer is an Apple IIe, and 
since I am going to be starting up a new MegaTraveller campaign, I 
thought that this program could come in handy...
  The hard part is finding it.  I called GDW, on the EXTREMELY slim 
chance that there were a few copies gathering dust on a shelf in the back 
rooms somewhere, but no luck...
  Which brings us to this plea-- 
 
        Is there anyone online in this mailing list who has the original 
Traveller Merchant Prince program TRADER for the Apple II?  I would be 
willing to pay for it (if not an outrageous price), and would send a disk 
for it, if need be.
 
  Actually, the thing sounds rather interesting.  It supposedly had a 
sector generator, twenty-four starships, the Spinward Marches and the 
Solomani Rim sectors with hex numbers, UPPs, bases, trade 
classifications, allegiance, a tradeworld marking and an 
explored/unexplored marking.
  Any help in this area would be appreciated...
 
Now: Go ahead and ROFL at this poor Apple IIe user, riding my skateboard 
on the information superhighway! :)
