    'index' => 'aa077',
    'topic' => 'Islands Campaign new technology',
    'body' => 'Here\'s a summary of the new technology used by the ships I\'ve been
posting--thanks to Andy St. John for prompting me to undertake this
long-delayed project.

This file contains technology used by designs completed so far. It does not
contain everything the Alliance has developed, nor does it contain technology
that has not had rules written for it yet. Those things will be added in
latter versions, and some technology included here may be changed.

Each technology listing includes the name, official tech level, and year
developed (or 5631 if it was in service at the end of Steve\'s PBEM game).
Year developed is not necessarily the same as year entering service--much of
the AM technology didn\'t see much use until around 5650.

Enhanced Output Maneuver Drive (TL15/5631 AD):
Designed like normal M-Drive but with 80% normal size, 125% normal cost, and
125% normal crew.

Afterburning Power Plant (TL15/5631 AD):
Includes fusion rocket as part of power plant. Design like normal plant, but
cost is MCr5 per ton. Designer chooses amount of additional thrust to be
generated--this thrust is limited by fuel and crew endurance. Endurance on
afterburner is calculated as follows:

      endurance (hours) = ln(((ship displacement) + (9.6 * fuel tonnage
allocated to afterburner)) / (ship displacement)) * (225 / acceleration due
to afterburner in Gs)

Laser Bay (TL13/5631 AD):
50 ton Pulse Laser Bay          50 ton Beam Laser Bay
  40 EP/Factor 8                  40 EP/Factor A
  60 EP/Factor 9                  60 EP/Factor B

100 ton Pulse Laser Bay         100 ton Beam Laser Bay
  80 EP/Factor A                  80 EP/Factor C
 100 EP/Factor B                 100 EP/Factor D

Cost is the same as a Particle Accelerator Bay of the same size.

Laser Spinal Mount (TL13/5631 AD):
Type      Tonnage        Pulse Factor     Beam Factor
Light      1000T              E               J
Medium     2000T              L               N
Heavy      4000T              Q               R
SuperHvy  12000T              V               W

Cost and \'To Hit\' is as for PA mount of same factor. Cost for SuperHeavy
mounts is:
Laser-V, MCr2250; Laser-W, MCr1686

NH3 Fuel System (TL14/5631 AD):
Uses ammonia as fuel--it is run through a special refinery before use,
splitting it into nitrogen and hydrogen. The NH3 takes up 52% of the space
required by hydrogen fuel. The refinery costs double the normal amount. Also,
a jump-capable ship using NH3 needs a special refinery to process the jump
fuel. This special refinery is ten times the normal size (and costs double
the normal amount as well).

Missile-A Bay (TL14/5631 AD):
An ordinary 100-ton missile bay built at TL14.

Acceleration Tank (TL12/5632 AD):
Allows crews on high-thrust ships to function. Compensates 12Gs with
oxygenated flourocarbons (a breathable liquid). A tank using oxygen
compensates 2G--this is what\'s included in TNE. No extra cost or tonnage.

Antimatter Warhead (TL18/5631 AD):
Acts just like a normal nuclear warhead, but is unaffected by nuclear
dampers. Each missile requires 1g of antimatter.

Antimatter Particle Accelerator Weapon System (TL18/5636 AD):
Design as a normal PA of any size. Does 1 surface hit, 2 radiation hits, and
destroys one armour factor per factor by which APAWS exceeds the target\'s
size code. Once the target\'s armour is gone, it does 1 surface hit, 3
radiation hits, and 1 critical hit for the same increment. Uses 10g of
antimatter per shot.

Matter/Antimatter Reaction Assembly (TL18/5634 AD):
Design like normal power plant. Percent of ship required for a plant of Pn
size is: 0.0185Pn, cost is MCr6.75/ton, consumes 8.75kg per EP generated per
year of antimatter.

Antimatter Jump Drive (TL18/5649 AD):
Design as normal jump drive. Fuel consumption per ton per parsec jumped is
100g antimatter and 100g normal matter.

ER Missile (TL13/5631 AD):
Capable of engaging targets beyond sensor range (out to 3 million km).
Requires an "ER missile gunner" crewmember aboard a unit within normal combat
range of target to provide guidance, one gunner per ER missile battery. One
battery-round of ER missiles requires 1.5T for 50T battery, 3T for 100T
battery. No extra cost.

Multi-Turret/Multi-Bay System (TL13/5631 AD):
Allows a craft to carry turrets or bays beyond the normally allowed number.
Each extra turret or bay takes twice the normal tonnage.

Oversize Bay (TL13/5631 AD):
Allows bays more powerful than the normal maximum to be built. For each extra
factor, double size, cost, and power consumption.

Meson Weapon (TL11/5644 AD):
These are included because the Islands Cluster didn\'t have meson technology
originally.

Kinetic Energy Missile (TL7/5633 AD):
Acts like nuclear warhead but unaffected by dampers or superconducting
armour. To hit penalty of -2.

Planetbuster Drone (TL18/5631 AD):
Designed like an unmanned fighter with an antimatter warhead requiring
5T/MCr100. To hit penalty -6 for early models, a hit destroys any ship.

Project Starburst (TL14/5646 AD):
Turn gas giants into small stars, or trigger flares (like Darrian) in
existing stars. Requires three meson guns firing in concert, each 100,000T
requiring 50,000EP.

Ablative Armour (TL14/5633 AD):
Each point of ablative armour counts in combat as 5 points of armour, one
point burns away with each hit.

Helson-Canomaar Overdrive (TL15/5636 AD):
Design as normal jump drive with double normal price, divide fuel requirement
by ten. H-C Overdrive may not be combined with an NH3 Fuel System (although a
ship can still use NH3 for its power plant) or Antimatter Jump Drive.

Antimatter Production Facility, Mark I (TL18/5631 AD):
Design as normal fusion power plant. Produces 15 grams of antimatter per EP
per year.

Antimatter Production Facility, Mark II (TL18/5650 AD):
Build as "habitat" from JTAS orbiting a gas giant. Size required is torus
with 150m cross section, outer diamter 10% larger than gas giant. Production
is 1 million tons of antimatter per year. Cost approximately MCr30 million.

Antimatter Production Facility, Mark III (TL18/5660(?) AD):
As above, but orbiting Gloire supernova remnant. Cost unknown, production 100
million tons of antimatter per year when completed.

Antimatter Containment Vessel (TL18/5631 AD):
Holds a ship\'s supply of antimatter safely. Each 1 tonne of AM contained
requires 1T/MCr3.

Shield (TL14/5638 AD):
Works by expelling a thick cloud of "sand" which is then suspended in a
magnetic field around the ship. Each shield unit generates one shield factor.
Units are built into 50T bays, cost MCr15, and require 5EP. Each shield
factor blocks three batteries of directed-energy fire before burning away.
Shields regenerate automatically every turn.

External Ordnance Rack (TL12/5633 AD):
Cost is MCr.1 per rack, 50 XO racks are equal to a single round of fire from
a Missile-A bay.

Antimissile Fire Control (TL13/5631 AD):
Allows a missile battery to fire defensively, acting as a repulsor battery 3
factors weaker. No cost.

Superconducting Armour (TL14/5635 AD):
Halves damage from lasers, nuclear and AM warheads. First point of armour
costs double.

Ken

