    'topic' => '1) Thanks 2) Questions: Core 3) Questions: World Builder\'s Guide',
    'body' => '
First: Thank you Steve Bonneville for sending the Core data!  I\'d download
       it here, but SOME people have to pay (gasp) for their e-mail...

Second: A few questions on the Core data...

        a) The data for Reference is D100100-B.  Why is there so few
people on Reference? I mean, this system is important enough to be on all
the \'Charted Space\' maps, but there are only 30 people!
           (And, if Reference was just a astrological point of
measurement, why Reference?  wouldn\'t Capital make a better choice?)
       
        b) Double Star (Core 0635) has only a _single_ star!  Yes, I know
his is nitpicking, but nits are to pick, after all.  Is there an \'offical\'
explanation for this?

Third: Thanks to Rodge Sanger (spelled from memory), I finally got a copy
       of the World Builder\'s Guide!  Horray! 

O.K., now on to the show...

  First: has anyone generated a "home system" for the Scouts?  Or, should I
say, where the largest Scout bases are (Perhaps in the Glimmerdrift
Reaches?)  

Second: Speaking of "culture centres"; Noble culture would be centered at
        Core, and \'archetypical\' Imperial Noble societies at 
                             Nimluin   2209  B476965-F
(All systems at TL F+,       Sanches   0416  A6549C9-F
 pop 9+)                     Sistar    1912  B430551-F
                           * Capital   2118  A586A98-F (Sylean, too)
(Incidentally, all 25 Sylean Ase       2219  B22098B-F 
systems are below TL B, with Kaskii    3218  A300A98-F
Capital, Khuir (Core 2513,   Irlu      0428  B53598C-F
B89AACA-D) and Rib (Core     Dral      0727  B728967-F
2314, B559667-F) being       Skeen     2226  B49199B-F
the sole exceptions...       Raami     2330  B522966-F
perhaps Vilani influences?)  Gurdaan   2623  B3109DA-F
                             Idas      2624  B4929AE-F
                             Night     0839  A5749C9-F
                             Aursis    1134  A5459BD-F
                             Khea      1836  B340955-F
                             Dishadshii2640  B614ACG-G (Lucan\'s birthplace?)
                             Igla      2837  B414ADG-F (Another choice...)
                             Saregon   2936  A6569BA-F   
                             Unlakhar  3040  B629997-G 

So, that\'s about 19 systems.  Most of the nobility, power, and decisions of
the Third Imp. would originate from here, with Capital taking a major
chunk of the whole.  
   
Third: The Imperial Military\'s patron was the sister of Strephon (if I
remember it right: what\'s her name again?).  Who was (ahem, _is_) the patron 
of the IISS?

Fourth: from the WBGuide: "To date, the Imperium considers such clones
[clones with the memory\'s of the original] to be quite illegal, since this
is \'tampering with the mind of a sentient lifeform, similar in concept to
psionics\' according to a ruling made by Emperor Paulo III in 1070"

Huh?  I knew that the Emperor had military and economic powers, but
judicial ones too?  Well, O.K... but no more Imperial suprises, or I\'ll
start wondering just how centralized IS the Third Imperium!

Also: how does the Emperor make these decisions?  By committe, who makes
it in his name? This seems plausable, but against my gut instinct.

By doing his homework, and then making his call? This seems likely.  But
now we have a single wo/man who has to be _at least_ compotent in the
fields of Macro-Macro economics, 
          BIG TIME Sociology, 
          Domain-wide Naval Strategy, and
          multi-racial, imperium-wide legal concepts.

(can you imagine Clinton I on the throne?  Oh, dear...) 

How many doctorates does Stephon _have_, anyways?

Even with the best of 10 trillion beings behind him, that\'s quite a load on
his shoulders...

Fifth: "Under no circumstances is the first open contact to be made with
weapons visible."  And which (beep) Imperial BUREAUCRAT made up THIS rule?
                   (and did anyone tell RCES?  giggle...giggle...)



