    'body' => 'Re Steve Charlton\'s comments on battledress doctrine
In 5FW, high tech units (presumably in BD) take a very long time to fall
when attacked by lower tech units; it seems to me that the same result
obtains in Invasion:Earth.  TL15+ units are also very difficult to bombard
effectively (see 5FW).  So it looks like they are just hard to kill.

What are probable doctrines for BD use?  Commandoes (Zhodani teleport
commandos [with or without the e?] wear BD)?  Situations where the BD troops
will be outnumbered by weakly armed (relatively) forces?  Or where insertion
of BD troops will force the defenders to turn important assets to tacking
tackling those troops, which will thus have importance out of proportion to
their number?

I don\'t have any problems with your melee weapon idea:  it is science
fiction.  U.S. Marines are very high tech troops today, and they\'re  trained
to use bayonets, knives, and even their entrenching tools as weapons.  Maybe
a bonded superdense titanium/vanadium edged cutlass in a Marine\'s
powered-armored hands would be a meaningful weapon in a close-quarters fight
(like on shipboard, where you might not want to fire plasma guns or RAM
grenades, to avoid damaging what you\'re trying to take or defend).

Cost-ineffective to arm BD troops with energy weapons?  Maybe not; you\'re
trying to protect your investment in the armor, too.

Kill all or no harm to any:  That, it seems from my reading, is often how
the world works (I do my level best to avoid finding out first hand).

