    'from' => 'sudet@well.sf.ca.us',
    'body' => 'David Reed started a nice discussion about what humaniti will look like and
believe in the far future, and I\'d like to see it develop further.  I hope
that there is someone on the TML who can tell me if the following facts are
correct:
The Ancients took humans from Terra about 300,000 years ago, and scattered
them among some 46 planets that we know of in Traveller times (I\'m pretty
confident about this fact).
Cro-magnon flourished 35 to 40,000 years ago.
Neanderthal flourished 35 to 100,000 years ago.
Cro-magnon, neanderthal, and some other groups were interfertile.
Races developed on Terra some 10,000 years ago.
The humans that the Vilani encountered when they began exploiting jump drive
were all interfertile.   (this is from DblAdv3, Research Station Gamma, at
21).
It would appear from the foregoing that the Vilani and Zhodani could have
been as different from the human strains on Earth as the neanderthals were
to modern caucasions, for example.  Intermarriage among the Vilani and the
other races absorbed into the Vilani empire might have led to the
development of still other racial types, and would also have blurred the
"racial purity" of the Vilani from Vland.  The Solomani conquest would have
done the same.
The Vilani and Zhodani had 300,000 years of development.  They may well have
developed different races in relatively different times within the general
group "Vilani" or "Zhodani" just as the Solomani had several different races
when they discovered jump drive.
I was glad to see that GDW adheres to position that there will be great
diversity in space; I don\'t know if any other view is remotely realistic.
