    'from' => 'sudet@well.sf.ca.us',
    'body' => 'Further to David Reed\'s comments on these subjects, my father put them in
special category of "subjects not to be discussed in [seamen\'s] bars."
What do we have in the way of religion in the far future?  The Vilani have
some sort of general ethical code that emphasizes tradition and community,
and does not seem to have a numinous aspect, at least in popular literature.
The only major religion that I\'ve discovered in the canon is the Church of
the Stellar Divinity, described in DblAdv 6: Divine Intervention, at 6-7, as
a very popular church that places few demands on its members and does not
interfere with government.  Church dogma is mainly that each star is a
divine being.  (See also Chellenge #44 Lost Treasures of the Abyss Rift;
MegaTraveller J. #3 at 97, news article).  The Church was founded in -3883,
during the Ziru Sirka (MegaTraveller J, supra).

The canon identifies many other small religions, like the Irklan of
Menorb/SpinwardMarches; the Society for the Sovereignty of Man over Machine
(based on Terra, I think); the religion of Jokotre/Spinward Marches that
is based on worship of the local deity Ram.
Another religion with some size is the Brotherhood, described in Alien
Realms as a human cult that believes that humaniti is destined to take over
the place of the Ancients in the universe.  It is widespread in Rhylanor
subsector, and has similar organizations in other areas.  (Alien Realms at
45).

So my questions to the TML are
-do you (other refs) have a place for the church as an instrument of the
state, or as a foil (or maybe neither)?
-what effect did the psionics suppressions have on public attitudes toward
religion (especially the numinous/mystical/altered consciousness aspects)?
-are there any broad (Imperial wide) religions?

