Subject: Re: Traveller Software

Thank you for volunteering, Jim!
 I\'ll send more to you off-line. I did want to answer some
of your comments for the list.
 
>     Do Loren\'s recent postings put a damper or change your original
>idea for this software? I thought the idea of typing in your own data
>was a pretty good one. Do you have any thoughts on this?

 My thoughts on Loren\'s recent and previous postings are simple:
"He has to say that." He really has no choice. I order to retain
copyright on their materials GDW has to be seen to discourage anyone
at all times from copying any of their stuff.
 Note: the key word in that last statement is "seen". I really,
honestly and truly doubt that GDW would ever consider taking me to
court for, say, SYSGEN. Hell, it is inarguably Traveller based and
if you asked them they would, indeed, say it was a violation and I
could be prosecuted.
 But why should they? They would only lose money. What they are
technically preventing is the establishment of Traveller as "public
domain" and someone else selling enough Traveller material to impact
on their market share. Do you really think they are going to spend
$10,000+ suing some half-arsed net programmer distributing shareware?
 I\'m sure if you dragged Loren into some quite corner and got
him drunk he would admit as much. However, whenever asked he will always
say that it is in violation of copyright and GDW is within its rights
if it chooses to sue.
 Careful readers will have noted that he has never jumped out
and said anything about this *without being asked*. If you ask, he
replies. If you don\'t ask, he doesn\'t. (As he purportedly doesn\'t
read the XTML he probably won\'t reply to this. If he did he would
probably replay as predicted.)
    Jo Grant
