believed that they WERE gods.  

Hitler had children begin their prayers "Our Furher, who art in Berlin..."
Stalin, Napoleon, Mao and that N. Korean guy had personality cults. 

What does the Emperor of the Third Imperium believe?

B) All enduring societies had a single religious/philosophical viewpoint,
which motivated and justified their actions.  The examples from ancient
history are too numerous and obvious to mention.

Modern Western societies have an anti-religious - especially, anti-Christian
- viewpoint.  Until recently, Eastern Europe worshipped Dialitical
Materialism, and had a large set of rituals and doctrines connected with
