In terms of volume.  I don\'t have MT with me today, so I couldn\'t say if
the saving in mass on the smaller fuel tank  will make up for the increased
mass of the fuel.

> > Besides, there\'s a far better way to improve fuel performance. Use D2 
> > instead of H2!
> 
>  Can\'t make the assumption that D is used to fuse, instead of H.  

Besides, if you look in the old TML files, you should find a message where 
I calculated that (in MegaTrav) a TL15 fusion plant produced more energy 
from each unit of fuel than could be accounted for by fusion of the naturally
occurring deuterium--so some protium fusion _must_ be going on, given those
fuel consumption rates.

I agree about the balance of the hydrogen probably being used as a heat
transfer working fluid, so nitrogen would proably work for that, too.

Rob Dean
robdean@access.digex.net

