    'topic' => 'Expanded Trade Rules',
    'body' => 'Ah, someone else who doesn\'t like the MT/TNE trade rules.

Somewhere around here I have a system I worked out that\'s an expansion of
Book 2.  (As I created it 3 moves ago, finding the files could be
interesting.)  Basically it is guidelines for creating a unique Book 2-style
"cargo encounter table" for every world: cargo frequency and size depend on a
world\'s World Builders Handbook resources (agricultural worlds having more
agricultural products available); cargo variety depends on population and
society (larger populations and fragmented societies give more types of
export); chances of finding a \'good deal\' depend on Trader; Broker is of
course useful for negotiating a better price; every cargo can have unique
handlign characteristics; etc.

I used this system in one trading campaign.  Worked well; my players even
enjoyed packing the hold (we used little cardboard crates on a deck plan).

I\'ll try to dig up the notes and upload them here.
