    'ts-index' => '1994-09-29.aa187',
    'body' => 'I\'ve been a big fan of Stutterwarp since I first read it in 2300AD. It\'s been
far and away my favorite FTL system ever since.

I haven\'t min/maxed Stutterwarp against the other means of FTL propulsion in
FF&S, but I\'m not surprised that it comes out to be incredibly efficient. IN
fact, I believe GDW had a warning to that effect, and recommended some kind
of limitation be generated by the GM. In 2300AD, the limit was that some
"stuff" builds up on the tantalum coils, stuff that is highly radioactive.
It has to be discharged every 7.7 light-years, or Bad Things happen. It must
be discharged in a gravity well of .1g or higher, I believe.

My question on stutterwarp is: what\'s the mass or volume? (I know one, but the
other is definitiely not iterated.) I was doing a comprehensive set of
star drive types for a GURPS campaign and converted Stutterwarp to GURPS
Vehicles stats, but was unable to figure either the mass or volume - I forget
which and I don\'t have my notes with me.


