    'index' => 'aa207',
    'month' => '10',
    'body' => 'I have the first five issues of this little mag, and it seems to be 
improving rapidly.  The first four are digest size (same as the Classic 
Traveller books), the fifth and latest is larger (8.5x11).  Cover art is 
now color, interior art is semi-pro.  This is a definite improvement from 
issue 1 (I haven\'t seen such ugly cover art since Judges Guild went out 
of business).  Issue six is due out this month.

Content is fair.  There is nothing as good as some of the stuff Digest 
Group put out, but it\'s as good as the stuff we are seeing in Challenge 
these days.  One nice thing is that they have a lot of background 
material (a four part series updating the Astrogator\'s Guide to the 
Diaspora sector, a similar series on the Far Frontiers sector, other 
background stuff).  There is also at least one adventure each issue, plus 
NPC and equipment descriptions.  The overall feel is much like the old 
Journal of the Travellers Aid Society, though not quite up to that 
quality (yet; they are definitly improving).

Published by:  Sword of the Knight Publications, Inc.
  2820 Sunset Lane #116
  Henderson, KY 42420
  502-826-1218
Editor: Kevin D. Knight
Assoc. Editor: Brenda K. Knight
Contributing Editor: J. Paul Sanders

I just noticed that they list an e-mail address in issues four and five:

  sword.knight@genie.geis.com

If you contact them you might want to ask them if they know about this 
list - I\'m sure they would be interested.

 
