    'topic' => 'Colonization in the 3rd Imperium',
    'body' => 'No colonization wasn\'t thwarted or impossible to do legally.  Look at the
Forboldn Project (Adventure 1: The Kinunir, at 39-40):

"The primary colonization project within the Regina subsector.  Originally
conceived in 987 to utilize the resources of Forboldn (0208), the project
began its execution phase in 1089, shortly after the Fourth Frontier War."

The library data entry goes on to describe the massive recruitment of
convicts and medical cases, refers to the Ministry of Colonization, and
intimates that colonization is ongoing and well regulated.

Anyway, as to your question of who administers colonization, it appears to
be the Ministry of Colonization.  I would guess that local political
situations would dictate additional kibbitzing, interference, or other input
from the IISS, the Navy, the local nobility, and the megacorporations.

