    'month' => '10',
    'topic' => 'New Alliance ship',
    'body' => 'Here\'s another new ship.

BB.1 St. Genevieve BB-S656(7)AJ4-E(V0)0700-D00SA-0 MCr375,812 250,000 tons
bearing                                    W  1Y   Crew=2997.
batteries                                  X  1Z   TL=15.
Passengers=30. Low=1499. Cargo=8709. Fuel=43,009. EP=25,015. Agility=6(7).
Marines=1200. 75,000 XO Racks.       V=40, W=39, X=60, Y=195, Z=300

Notes: Has NH3, enhanced output m-drive, H-C overdrive, superconducting
armour, anti-missile fire control. Carries 3 30-ton small craft, 1 95-ton
small craft, 5 90-ton planetbusters. Has 9000 ton missile magazine (3000
battery-rounds), 650 ER missile gunners, 5 tonne AM containment pod, 1500
battery-rounds in XO racks, 12 parsecs jump fuel.

Development of this class began shortly after the Topas War. At that time,
FAdm Connor had proclaimed that the _Excelsior_ class battleship was the best
in the Cluster. The NFN was understandably proud of this praise, but they\'d
also realized that the new technologies being developed would soon make the
old ships obsolete. The NFN Battleship Design Team went to President Krieg
with a proposal for a new battleship, one which would be superior to the
_next_ generation of Cluster battleships, and able to go one-on-one with
Imperial battleships. President Krieg gave the go-ahead.

The _St. Genevieve_ was laid down at Sansterre in late 5630. The ship saw one
substantial redesign prior to the Serendip War, and then the Imperials
arrived. The NFN team that had designed the ship was stationed on New Home\'s
Station Omega for the Occupation, while the battleship continued to be built
on Sansterre under the supervision of Sansterre\'s ship design teams. This
lead to the controversial aspect of the _St. Genevieve\'s_ design.

With the availability of such things as H-C overdrive, another redesign was
needed. The NFN team put out a revision that used the space freed up by the
reduced fuel requirement to mount a heavy energy armament, centered on two
Factor-S spinal mounts--one meson and one APAWS. The Sansterran team had
different ideas--Sansterran warships emphasized missile firepower rather than
energy weapons, and they went ahead and modified the battleship according to
their own philosophy.

The NFN team was very angry that their energy-weapon battleship was instead
mounting 300 missile bays, and complained to the Alliance Naval Construction
Board. The NCB studied the situation, and decided that the ship would stand
as redesigned. The missile armament was deemed "good enough," and more
importantly it would take several more weeks to rebuild it the way the NFN
wanted it.

During the CLW, the _St. Genevieve_ performed admirably. FAdm Connor told the
Council that the ship was superior to all known battleships, even the
Imperial _Tigress_, and the NFN\'s ideas about what the ship should have been
were promptly forgotten as all subsequent battleship were built to Sansterran
specs.

Several of these battleships took part in the Battle of Quiver in 5648.
Although the battle was a total victory for the Alliance, it became apparent
that the Imperial Navy was beginning to modify ships on the Alliance border
with new technology that made them much more of a match for Alliance ships.
In 5649, the Alliance began refitting many of its ships with antimatter power
to maintain a technological edge over possible enemies.

The redesign saw the revival of the old NFN energy-weapon design. After
considerable lobbying, the Naval Construction Board agreed to allow one ship
to be equipped with heavy energy-weapons in 5650 as an experiment. If the
ship is a success, other battleship may also be modified.

Ken

