    'from' => 'Jeff Scott Franzmann umfranzm@cc.UManito',
    'body' => 'On Sun, 9 Oct 1994, Mitchell K Schwartz wrote:

> Since Loren has never paid any attention to my opinions regarding TNE in the
> last year and a half, I am not in much awe of his.

Difference of opinions, I\'d expect. However, having a different opinion
doesn\'t invalidate an opposite postion.

> I have no objection, joy, or care as to his presence on this list.  Nor 
> do I expect we\'ll gain over much by it.  CT/MT is, after all, from his 
> point of view a dead project.

Ouch. A little touchy on this subject, I\'d guess :). While I myself am
fond of both Classic and Megatraveller, I seem to be one of the few people
on this list who actually LIKES the background of the New Era. I certainly
like the rules system more, simply due to the fact that it is (IMHO) more
coherent than the previous releases. I LOVED the Rebellion background, and
still maintain a campaign in that setting. However, I have an equal
fondness for the new background setting, and all the possibilities
inherent in it as well.

I wouldn\'t mind seeing a GDW presence here :).

Sincerely,
Jeff Franzmann

