    'topic' => ' Xboat Routes',
    'body' => '>I\'m producing Xboat maps of (unprinted) sectors.  I figured out the 
>postscript code for creating lines from one hex to another.  What I need is
>a reasonable set of rules for determining xboat paths. Anyone got any?

I use the following guidelines:
    4 jumps max (no mimimum since some lower jumps may be needed to keep a
       later jump 4 hexes or less)
    Jumps should go to systems with a) High Populations, b) Class A or B
Starports,
       c) Scout Bases.  d) A system that could feed several other worlds
with a jump 1
       (basic networking -- place your hubs, where you can easily feed your
satellites).

>Anyone know how they were determined in the first place?

There is little reason to the routes in the Spinward Marches.For instance,
the route from Risek (2712) to Dhian (2510) makes no sense except that  Paya
(2509) would only be a one hex feed from the route, and the route terminates
at Inthe (2410) one hex away.

Another oddity is the route from Lunion (2124) to Aeabicci (1824) to
Lanic(1924).  The route from Luniont o Aeabicci makes sense, but Lanic is a
one hex jump from Aebicci and Lanic is a Class E star port with no scout
base and from my Spinward Marches map doesn\'t classify for a large
population.

For the most part, the map follows simple networking basics (with a little
historic expansion put into things such as the route from Regina to Extolay
(3 - Jump 1\'s).

Rob
