    'body' => '
I\'d like to use the current X-boat route thread to remind
folks of one of DGP\'s less-known but DANDY oversights, namely:

Their X-Boat routes have this tendency to MISS the way stations!

Kinda embarassing, considering the WS\'s are maintainence and
routing hubs.

My solution was to re-place the WS\'s, since that was easier than
redrawing the map.

It also allowed me to correct another problem I noticed while
checking the "off-route" problem, namely in most sectors there
are too damn few Way stations.  Some sectors have as low as
three, while the Spinward Marches had five (even though the
Impeium only controlled half of it.

I settled on a "standard" density of 1WS per 2 subsectors.
Some areas (like Core and the Marches) would still be a little
above average, but it was easier to rationalize than before,
when they _really_ stood out.


John "so help me, I really did check over all those map hexes" Bogan
