X::>I\'m producing Xboat maps of (unprinted) sectors.  I figured out the
 ::>postscript code for creating lines from one hex to another.  What I need
is
 ::>a reasonable set of rules for determining xboat paths. Anyone got any?

 The rules I would be inclined to assume:

 1) No jump is longer than 4 Parsecs (this is required by the 
 design of the XBoat).

 2) Preference is given to A starports, though B can be used.  
 Connect eligible starports.

 3) A starports that are on worlds with less than population 6 may 
 be bypassed.

 4) C starports are only used to provide connections between A and 
 B starports that otherwise could not be connected.  No more than 
 one C starport may be used in a connection to a B starport; no 
 more than two C starports may be used to connect A starports.

 5) D, E, and X starports are never served.

 6) Sector capitals are always served by the XBoats.

 7) Subsector capitals will be served, regardless of starport, if 
 they are within J3 of a served planet.  If they are class A or B, 
 apply rules 2 and 3.

 On a few randomly generated test sectors, these rules worked 
 pretty well...
==========================================================================
Jeff Zeitlin                                      jeff.zeitlin@execnet.com
