    'body' => '   Hmmm, Darrians...I have this somewhere around here.  Alien Supplement #8,
I think.  Let\'s see what I remember.  They had a culture in advance of the
Imperium, tech 16 going on 17, due to a more peaceful history and the fact
that the Ancients dumped them on a world where they couldn\'t eat the food
without \'processing\' it first.  They carved themselves out a little 7 or 8
star region in the Spinward Marches, and had it pretty good.  Floating
cities,
etc.  Then they accidentally discovered the Star Trigger.  Not the classical 
\'making a star go boom\', but just shedding it\'s outer corona of gas quickly 
(like at near light-speed) with a massive EMP burst.  All electronics in the
system died (remember the floating cities?).  The wave travelled through the
rest of the Darrian Worlds, with lesser effect.  End result:  they dropped a 
couple of tech levels, still have a small fleet of T16 ships, and are almost 
back up to 16 again.  real cutting edge stuff.  No one wants to mess with the
Darrians, as they claim they can do that to _any_ system (don\'t mess with us,
or we\'ll wipe every grav module and computer you have).

Oh, yes, and the major cultural effect of the Maaghiz (sp?)/EMP blast was 
that they now build _everything_ with non-electronic backup.  Air/rafts with
wing/parachutes, hardened optical memory in their computers, etc.

Glenn
(not the one that posts all the time, but rather a newcomer)

