    'body' => 'ehenry@Newbridge.COM (Ethan Henry) says:

>This interview/massive-back-patting lists all the GDW publication up
>until 1987 and _doesn\'t_ list Darrians, so I guess it got shelved.
>Anyone know why? (Loren?) Not too much meat in this interview, but
>there are some more products I\'ve never seen - \'Alien Realms\' and
>\'Atlas of the Imperium\'. Anyone care to fill me in on what\'s in these?

 \'Darrians\' was indeed printed. I own a copy. It was, as far as I can
determine, the last CT product printed by GDW (outside of some Challenge
articles).

 \'Alien Realms\' is a scenario book which concentrates on the various
alien races. Each scenario involves either playing or being heavily
involved with one or more of the major races. Not a bad product aside
from its thinness.

 \'Atlas of the Imperium\' is a book of sector grids for the area shown
on all the standard "Imperial Space" maps in MT and TNE. All systems
were placed, and had the data that was normally shown on maps in
those days: dry or wet world, gas giants, port rating, bases, and
allegiances. Only High Population worlds were named, though, and XBoat
routes were absent.  The sector files available from the old archives
were the basis for this book. I\'m told that GDW will consider reprinting
the Atlas if they get enough requests (like enough to pre-sell most of the
print run), but won\'t do so otherwise. Considering the wide-open nature
of TNE and the prospect of "your very own Pocket Empire wherever you want"
I should think that reprinting the Atlas might be a good and desirable
thing, but this is the wrong list to be discussing such urges ;)


