    'body' => 'Here\'s the Sol-class carrier. With this ship, I\'ve finished posting the
Alliance Navy\'s NH3-fueled combatant starships (unless I forgot something
:-)).


CV-29 Sol CV-S456(7)7J4-4(R0)0700-0000A-50 MCr169,598.4 200,000 tons
bearing                               Y    Crew=2197.
batteries                             Z    TL=15.
Low=1099. Cargo=2396. Fuel=27,405. EP=14,239. Agility=6(7). Marines=250.
30,000 XO Racks.                          Y=33, Z=50

Notes: This ships uses the usual technology--enhanced output m-drive, H-C
overdrive, NH3 fuel, anti-missile fire control, superconducting armour,
afterburning plant. Has two computers. The ship uses modular construction,
and can be built in just over two years. The Sol-class, due to its modular
construction, has many components in common with the smaller modular designs.

Has 5 30-ton small craft, 10 parsecs jump fuel, a 1 tonne AM containment pod,
and space for 500 90-ton fighters (normally FA-5E Super Kraits). Has a
balcony and track launch system with balcony space for 250 fighters and a
track able to move up to 250 per turn. Has 600 battery-rounds of fire in XO
racks. Unlike nearly every other Alliance warship, this class does not have
an ER missile magazine.

The Sol-class has a small portable shipyard with a capacity of 1800 tons.
This allows up to 20 fighters to be repaired or even constructed at one time.
The Sol-class carrier is the first warship type to use this system.

The Sol-class was designed as a replacement for the smaller Eagle- and
Nimitz-class carriers used by the Alliance Navy. The Alliance Navy wanted its
new carrier to have a fighter group capable of putting an enemy battleship
out of action with one strike. A 500-fighter group was selected, and the
carrier design combined Sansterran construction techniques with Neubayern
carrier systems.

The Sol-class carriers have seen action in both the Sarage and Quiver
Campaigns. During these actions, they proved that their fighters could indeed
take out battleships with one salvo. Although even 500 fighters generally
can\'t destroy a battleship outright, they were able to destroy their target\'s
maneuver drives. With their m-drives gone, the Imperial battleships had no
choice but to jump away or face destruction by a meson gun-equipped cruiser.

The Alliance Navy regards a carrier as equivalent in strategic terms to a
battleship (and when the fighter group is included, it costs almost as much),
and deploys them accordingly. Since a meson gun is needed to force ships that
have lost their m-drive but can still fight to leave the area, carriers are
generally accompanied by Sol Bianca-class light cruisers.

The Sol-class was built to carry fighters with two-person crews (such as the
Krait), but the new Cobra has a crew of four. The Alliance Navy plans to add
new crew quarters when carriers are refitted with AM power, and only deploy
Cobras on the refitted carriers, but if it should be necessary to fly Cobras
off unrefitted carriers an additional 500 crew staterooms can be installed in
the cargo bay.

Ken
