    'body' => 'Markc@csos.orst.edu (mark f. cook) asked what SORAG means...

MARK:  That depends on who you ask.  According to "official" publications 
of the Zhodani Consulate, SORAG stands for: Study and Operations 
Recording Activities Group", and is a division of the Zhodani Consulate 
Combined Interstellar Forces that observes the progress of emerging 
interstellar societies using overt and passive means.

  According to more accurate, Top Secret sources, SORAG stands for: 
Scientific Operations Research and Administration Group, and is an 
intelligence and counter-intelligence service operated by the Colonade 
Administrative District (CAD) in the Vanguard Reaches (a Zhodani 
Administrative District).  These sources report that SORAG\'s missions 
include: guerilla warfare, subversion, sabotage, escape and evasion, 
"black" and "grey" psychological operations, etc.

  Try finding the SORAG booklet (it will be extremely difficult).  It was 
an excellent little item, designed and written by Chuck Kallenbach II, 
one of the better-known members of the HIWG (History of the Impireum 
Working Group).
  Actually, try getting any of the Paranoia Press supplements...they are 
all very good add-ons to CT (and even to MT, with a little tweaking).
