headquarters on Asimikigir (Amdukan 0223), and provide intra-JP
dispute mediation, interstellar laws, and a standing armed force for
patrols and crisis situations (the Star Legion). It also has bodies
which promote interstellar trade and communication.

Culturally, the JP features a great deal of human/Vargr
cooperation. This reaches its pinnacle on Asimikigir, which is a true
"dual-species culture" - in fact, humans and Vargr on Asimikigir get
along better with each other than they do with different ethnic groups
of their own species.

When the Long Night began, Vargr raiders attacked this region in
force, most brutally at Gashikan, a garden world which had nuclear
weapons used against it. This prompted a strong anti-Vargr reaction
which resulted in Vargr being stripped of their civil rights on most
worlds and subject to outright slavery. As the region recovered, one
of the most powerful forces was the Menderes trading corporation,
owner of millions of enslaved Vargr. An insightful company head
eventually realized race-hatred was bad for business, and turned its
slaves into employees. Humans and Vargr began to work together from
this point, as many states began emancipating their Vargr because of
the benefits of cooperation.

The Julian War (175-191) was an attempt by Martin I to reclaim the old
Ziru Sirka territories in the region. Fearing the region would be
conquered by the Imperium under a pretext of reclaiming the
Makhidkarun areas, the Menderes corporation stirred up anti-Imperial
sentiment, and the humans and Vargr of the area rallied to its
charismatic head, Julian Menderes. The confederations of the area 
created the united Star Legion which, under Julian, repulsed the
Imperial fleets and pressed into the Imperium itself before the latter
sued for peace. "Julian\'s" conferedation dates from this time.

Something which must be mentioned along with the JP is the Third
Empire of Gashikan. Gashikan was mentioned above as a world which had
nuclear wepaons used against it by Vargr. It is, in some sense, the
"Anti-Asimikigir"; Vargr are killed on sight on its surface, and many
other worlds in the Empire still enslave Vargr. The primary cultural
conflict in the JP area is the tolerance of the JP vs. the bigotry of
the Empire. (The Empire is not really a serious threat to the JP, 
technologically, economically, or militarily.)

The symbol of the JP is a Trojan helmet in profile (Menderes comes
from "Maiandros", the name of the river flowing past ancient Troy.) In
1118 when Antares joined, it changed to three solid triangles
surrounding the helmet to form an inverted equilateral triangle
with the helmet at the center.

Yes, there is one other significant alien race in the region, the
cigar-smokin\' Hhkar.

(To add to my previous "regional stereotypes" message: citizens of
Vland sector never refer to the JP as the JP, only as the "coreward 
Makhidkarun territories".)
