    'topic' => 'UWP Generation - a brief addition',
    'body' => '
It seems that most of the folks here prefer to make "fun new specices" and
unusual explanations for odd worlds (ie. 20 million people with a chewable
atmosphere and victorian technology) rather than \'fix the system\', aas Jim
recommended.

So, it would follow that in your Imperiums (rather than "MY" Imperium), a
major fraction of the imperial population consists of non-human and
Altered-human populations, say from 10% to 50%.  This varies from "MY"
Imperium (and, I think, the "Official" Imperium), where the Imperial
population is something like 90% Solomani/Vilani, and most of the rest
Vargr and Aslan, with a springling of other races.

You know, I find "YOUR" Imperiums more interesting... any space to move in?
----
On a related topic, how does a heavily non-human interstellar empire
function differently than a heavily-human polity?  

Things that come to mind....
   Language & culture conflicts.    (reminicent of India, with it\'s 17
                                     offical languages.  The British Raj 
                                     with jump drive!)
   Enviromental problems.           
       ... How does the Imperial Navy handle all those atmospheres & grav\'s?
           I think that "specices-specific" ships would be the norm, with
           the favoured Loyal/Martial races having single-species squadrons
           (ie. the Irish Regiment, the dominant Skih element in the
           Indian Army, etc.) Or mabye not - ie. the desegretation of the
           U.S. Army - but I thing that it would be prohibively expensive
           to build one ship that would meet all those standards (and sustain
           battle-damage, too!)
    Trade problems.
       ... Trade would be interesting, to put it mildly.  "Startown" would   
           take on a whole new meaning - not only is it the \'contact
           point\' for the trading and multi-system community, but it would 
           be a madcap mess of atmospheres, languages, ultra-frigid bars
           next to 6 grav gyms...   (why can I hear the the Mos Elseley band
           playing faintly in the background?)
    Diplomatic problems.
       ... I\'d like to imagine the workload that the Imperial Diplomatic
           Core would have.  Especially when some glint-eye religion,  
           Vargr incursion or unthinking megacorp upsets the applecart...
           And what about Ancient Emmities between heavyweights in the
           same subsector?  Who can\'t even understand each other mental
           concepts?  Fun fun fun!
    Government problems.
       ... the idea of a nobility has to be among the most basic,
           easily-understood government-type in history.  (See him?
           With the Guns and the Money? He makes the rules!)  Even so, 
           I wonder how all those aliens precieve the Imperium...  
           How does a incorporal hive mind understand the concept of   
           "taxes"?   Does that large, 16-legged, TL D "spideroid"
           really grasp how the xboat network operates?  [Or maybe \'he\'
           really does understand it, just... differently... than we do.]

All in all, simply too much.  I have enough problems with a handful of
Altered (& Standard) humans in my campaign.  I can\'t imagine handling the
~100 species in the Third Imperium, even with Solomani/vargr dominance.  And
now you expect me to try to handle thousands of species ...in the trilions
of population...a dozen or more species per subsector?     

.. and I thought that being Emperor of the "Official" Imperium was
overwelming...
 
Alvin Plummer
("When your players complete an adventure session, their characters oughta
to recieve suitable rewards")

P.S. Any word on who Plankwell is, and why he assassinated the Emperess
     Josephine?


