X::>I may have asked this question previously, but, just in case I didn\'t...

X::>Why did the Sword Worlders breakup into the Sord World Federation and the
 ::>Sword World Union a.k.a. The BorderWorlds?

X::>Any data would be appreciated...

 As I recall, this was an aftereffect of the Fifth Frontier War.
 The Sword Worlds Confederation was part of the Outworld Coalition,
 which was defeated by the Third Imperium.  I seem to recall something
 about a pro-Imperial (or at least less anti-Imperial) faction 
 based on Sacnoth, which, after the Imperial defeat (and 
 occupation?) of the Coalition, was able to seize power (with 
 [covert?] Imperial help?) in the trailing worlds of the 
 Confederation.  Why they chose "Sword Worlds Union" rather than 
 something else entirely is unclear to me - unless they were 
 claiming to be the legitimate government of the _entire_ Sword 
 Worlds, the government on Gram notwithstanding.
