    'body' => 'Just my addition,
 POP: I always assume that the pop figure does not
include transients. Thus where you have a naval base or
a large itinerant labour base this will not be accounted
for in the POP figures. (There are no aliens in my
universe. Humans are diverse and strange enough :-)
 TECH: I always assume the Tech Level is the level
of technology that a particular planet can *produce*.
Obviously a Tech Level 3 society on an airless world
still needs to have domes/air-management systems. However
they may be incapable of producing them for themselves.
Thus they have to import them.
 This is perfectly reasonable. I live in Ireland.
There are many "high-tech" things which our society
depends on (e.g. the busses of our public transport
system!) that are not, and can not, be made in this
country.
 These two assumptions generally cover most
any "funny" UWP rating. As my campaign setting is
entirely computer generated I don\'t really have
the chance to tweak anything. Never been a problem.

    Jo

