    'body' => 'Yep, Far Traveller had only 2 issues.

As for Spinward Marches and surrounds:

	The Domain of Deneb (Spinward Marches, Deneb, Trojan Reach, and Reft
	Sector are displayed in a map that was included in MegaTraveller
	Journal #1 by DGP.  The UWP data to go with the map was presented
	in MegaTraveller Journal #3.

	Trojan Reach was developed in The Third Imperium, one of the better
	Traveller fanzines.  A subsector was presented in 10 of its 11 issues,
	along with further development included in each issue\'s feature
	adventure.  TI retained the placement of worlds presented in GDW\'s
	Atlas of the Imperium, and DGP retained TI\'s world names and UWP\'s
	in its portrayal of Trajan Reach in Traveller\'s Digest #20 (which
	includes a sector map, data listings in the expanded format, a feature
	adventure set in Trojan Reach, and Library Data for the sector), MTJ1,
	& MTJ3.  In all, counting the 2 subsectors developed in GDW\'s 
	Adventure 4 - Leviathan, a total of 12 out of the 16 subsectors of
	Trojan Reach were developed on the subsector level (that I know of).

	Foreven Sector (one sector spinward of the Spinward Marches) was 
	developed in The Imperium Staple by Herb Petro (of the HIWG), starting
	in issue #6.  Two subsectors (Reidan, Urnian) and one planet (Hold/
	Reidan) were developed.  GDW later published a map of Foreven in
	Imperial Lines, which only showed  planet positions, and the map 
	did not retain the planet positions presented in Imperium Staple.
	Herb Petro allegedly developed much more of the sector.

	Far Frontiers was fasa\'s "land grant", and they published 6 adventures
	set there, including the popular Sky Raiders trilogy by J. Andrew
	Keith.  Fasa presented but a single subsector map (Jungleblut), and
	4 of the 6 adventures contained library data on the sector.  Dale
	Kemper designed the sector, and he submitted half of it to TSR
	which published it in Ares special edition #2.  This same article
	was expanded and reprinted in The Traveller Chronicle, which is
	also publishing the other half of the sector.  FYI, Far Frontiers
	is 2 sectors spinward of the Spinward Marches.

That\'s about all the time I have for now.  I hope the above info helps.

Sincerely,
Roger Sanger
