Just a couple of additional support arguments.  You can not include navel
and scout facilities in the population counts because there are some worlds
(the wonders of computer generation no doubt) that has a class A starport,
Navel base and a population of 8 (UWP code 0, pop modifier 8).  Obviously 8
people cannot run a starship repair facility.  Typically in these cases the
starport is orbital only with a class E on the surface and the people who
run the star port are not included in the count.

As far as aliens go, there is a world in Deneb whos TL is 0-3 (cant remember
off the top of my head), the UWP pop code is a 7 or 8 and its an airless
world.  On top of that, its Interdicted (red zone).  So without any details
available on the system I determined that for my campain that there were
millions of sentient silicon life forms that were developing on their own.
So in this case the local population had to include non-human life (also
consider Vargr and Aslan space :-)  )

Rob
