Well, the histories we have don\'t dwell on Imperial blunders, but
consider the following (dates are birth-coronation-death):

Martin I (12-166-195): lost the Julian War
Cleon IV (423-475-555): probably murdered Nicholle and her family, 
   obtained Moot approval by blackmail of and threats against its members
Zhakirov (624-666-688): married a filthy Vilani and put the Imperium
   in the pockets of the Zirunkariish bankers (oops, I guess SolSec
   inserted that...)
Paula II (752-768-836): instantiated the Psionic Suppressions -
   whether or not this was a blunder is a matter of opinion
Styryx (920-945-989(abdication)): presided over the "mismanaged" 
   Third Frontier War

Of this list, Cleon IV (a "nondynastic interloper") sounds the most
disgraceful on the face of it.

A special award goes to Marava (551-620-620) for destroying the Grand
Palace of Martin II on Capital. Civil War or no Civil War, destroying
monuments of the Imperium is just Not Done.

-Erich
