    'topic' => 'Running post-5FW campaigns',
    'body' => 'Roger Sanger asked who\'s running campaigns set in the Spinward Marches after
the Fifth Frontier War.  I am (as Rodge knows).  I\'ve been running the same
campaign since 1989, but we are lucky to play once or twice a year, because
my continuing character and I tend to move to opposite sides of the country.
We started in mid-1107, and we\'re up to late 1107.  I\'ve played the 5FW
boardgame solo many turns in advance, and kept track of unit positions, so i
know what the players will encounter as they travel in Regina subsector (and
throughout the war zone).  I prepared forms listing each world in the first
column and then having six columns for turns on each form:
world      turn 18      turn 19     etc
Joyeuse    SWJoyFl n/f  SWJoyFl     _____

The record keeping is a hassle.

Mark Clark wrote that he had created an index card for each world in the
Spinward Marches, and then noted on it each piece of published information
about that world.  I thought I was the only person who was so compulsive,
and now I learn that Mark and Rodge are, too.  I eventually put it all into
a huge WordPerfect document, with one-page entries for each world, including
all CT and MT information in my possession.  WP may not be the best
software for this, but it works ok.

What are other referees doing?
