    'date' => 'Wed, 9 Nov 1994 13:18:40  0600',
    'body' => 'George Herbert <gherbert@crl.com> writes:

>Plankwell is (the late) Admiral of the Marches Olav haut-Plankwell (if I
>remember exactly).  He was the naval commander in the Spinward Marches
>when the first frontier war broke out (589?), and there was some problem
>with lack of support from the rest of the Imperium during that war, which
>led to the later events.

There\'s enough info floating around to expand on this a bit.  Remember
that Jacqueline was *elected* Empress by the Moot; before that, she
was likely an archduke or other high-ranking noble, but we don\'t know
from where.  However, she was the one who decided to open the rimward
frontier of the Imperium -- Terra joined the empire in 588, just one
year before the First Frontier War began.  It looks like she really
wasn\'t that interested in the region "behind the claw".  (Maybe she
was the Archduchess of Sol or supported by those interests in the
Moot -- before the late 500s, Sol would not have included much of
Old Expanses or Solomani Rim, at least.)

The library data suggests that Jacqueline was transferring the Imperial
focus from the spinward regions (where it had been concentrated for
over half a millenium) to the rimward regions.  Then, when the 1FW
broke out, Imperial reaction was slow, and all the settlements in 
Foreven and some in the Marches were lost.  This may have been partly
caused by Imperial indifference to the previously peaceful Marches 
at the highest levels.  (Possibly combined with a fear that the
cultural Solomani would form a non-Imperial state to rimward if not
soon absorbed.)

This mirrors events following the conclusion of the *other* Frontier
War the Imperium lost big, the Third.  At it\'s conclusion, a palace
coup engineered by General Dienne of the Imperial Guard forced Styryx 
to resign in favor of his son, Gavin -- too late to stop the Solomani
Rim War, though.  (Dienne made him abdicate at the gunpoint of his
gauss pistol, when he found Styryx cowering in a \'fresher in the 
Imperial Palace.) 

(I\'m being nice about the 2FW, but Arbellatra was working with only
the meager resources of the sparsely-settled Marches, and I doubt
Cleon V and his numerous successors of the same mind were able to
help her with much.)

  Steve Bonneville
  <bonn0015@gold.tc.umn.edu>
