    'body' => 'PF.41 Tsunami PF-A606(C)LJ2-400700-0000A-0 MCr1225.6 1000 tons
bearing                                2   Crew=25.
batteries                              2   TL=15.
Fuel=200. EP=202. Agility=6(12). 500 XO Racks.

Notes: Uses enhanced output m-drive, superconducting armour, and anti-missile
fire control. Carries 10 ER missile gunners.

The Tsunami fast patrol boat is not used by the Alliance Navy\'s "regular"
forces, but it is a mainstay of the System Skywatches. Since the class was
introduced in 5641, several thousand have been built for Alliance members,
and hundreds more have been exported to friendly governments in the Trojan
Reach and Riftspan Reaches.

The principle duty of the Tsunami is to patrol a system, enforce the law, and
respond to emergency calls--in short, it\'s a spacegoing police car. As such,
most Navy encounters in Alliance space will be with patrolling Tsunamis.

In combat, the first priority for any PF is to destroy enemy fighters and
gunboats before they can bother Alliance starships. Imperial light combatants
are so pathetic that Tsunami crews hardly give them a second thought. The
fighters and gunboats of the more advanced Aslan Clans and the Florian League
are a different story, though. Tsunami crews regularly practice engagements
against their ships, and would expect to have a real fight on their hands in
an actual battle.

Once enemy light combatants are dealt with, the PFs would rearm their XO
racks and engage the enemy\'s cruisers and capital ships. In this role, they\'d
act just like overgrown fighters.

The original Alliance PF was the Thunderbolt, of which 40 were built. They
performed adequately during the CLW, but when the Alliance\'s new technology
was incorporated into a new PF design the design team decided to classify it
as a new class. The name refers to the effect they hoped it would have on
attacking forces. (And also as a tribute to the fate of Democratic candidates
in the recent U.S. elections, to whom I say: Welcome to the unemployment
line, you authoritarian scumbags!)

Ken
