    'body' => 'I will say first-off that I was not amused with receiving an XBoat digest
that was nothing but old posts - even though those posts had not been seen
by my eyes. Now, it was no big deal and I\'m over it ;) but it seems we are
still pondering a solution as to whether or not to have more digests
re-posted.

I don\'t think they should be. First of all, I enjoy more topical reading
material, and while the reprints may inspire new debate, I don\'t think
they\'re necessary to foster a new discussion. There\'s also the matter of
archiving. It is a waste of disk space to archive TML bundles that contain
the same material.

On the other hand, I sympathize those for whom diret perusal of these
archives is not feasible, whether due to facility or training.

Why not a compromise? Alvin can collect the addresses of all those who like
a copy of the old stuff mailed to them and can send it to them directly,
rather than posting to the list. That way we not only get rid of the
reprints, but all the discussion about whther or not they are acceptable
(which is worse, IMHO).


