>1) I have a question about why cargo costs don\'t are the same regarding the
>distance involved.  Why shouldn\'t a ship carrying a jump 2 (or 3, or
>whatever) cargo be able to charge a more than a ship carrying a jump 1
>cargo?  Fuel costs go up and it\'s still cheaper than several jump 1\'s.

        I multiply frieght-rates in my world by a co-effieicnt equal to the
twice the number of parsecs per week the ship can cover divided by the
distance to go.  So, a jump 1 ship carrying cargo at a distance of jump one
has a multiplier of 2 ( 2* 1 parsec per week / 1 parsec =1).  A jump 2 ship
carrying cargo a distance of 1 parsec also has a multiplier of 2.  However,
when we get to a 2 parsec trip, we get a pay off:

  Jump 2 Ship :  2 * 2 parsecs per week / 2 parsecs = mult of 2
  Jump 1 Ship :  2 * 1 parsec per week / 2 parsecs = mult of 1

        I have a base multiplier of x2, since as noted by others,
frieghters don\'t make enough hauling frieght to pay for themselves and not
everyone can trade by speculation.  In fact, the large proportion of modern
container ships don\'t own the goods on them.  I don\'t see why that would
change;  while speculative trade is certainly going to be a major aspect of
interstellar trade, it won\'t be the main-stay.  Not at the ship level,
anyway.
        Notice that while a Jump 1 ship can still make some profit in
servicing jump 2 lines, as soon as a Jp2 frieghter shows up, they are
toast.  The Jp2 ship can make twice as many runs, at twice the profit
level.
        A 4 parsec run creates an even greater shelf:

   Jump 4 Ship : 2 * 4 parsecs per week / 4 parsecs = 2
   Jump 2 Ship : 2 * 2 parsecs per week / 4 parsecs = 1
   Jump 1 Ship : 2 * 1 parsecs per week / 4 parsecs = 0.5

        The high-speed trader servicing way-ward trade routes with his Jp6
ship is going to make a killing under this system.  However, because of the
expense to maintain the ship (annual overhaul and more crew!) he will not
fair as well on a 1 parsec run against Jp1 ships;  thier maintenence and
operating expenses are less.
        In practice, what this does in my campaign is convinces players to
build Jp3 frieghters.  They can still get the mult 1 on cargo all the way
up to a 6 parsec haul, but get a mult 2 on 3 parsecs and shorter.
        Another thing this has done has led to the creation of the
Transporter ship.  Some cunning company buys a surplus and stripped
dreadnaught hull, bumps the engines up to jp6 and 6g\'s and takes the left
over space as HANGAR.  Got a Jp 2 ship that needs to make a Jp 6?  For 25%
of your trip profits, we\'ll take you there!  As a result, the frieghter
gets and effective mult of 1.5, and the Transporter can get 20 or 30 x .5
...
