>whatever) cargo be able to charge a more than a ship carrying a jump 1
>cargo?  Fuel costs go up and it\'s still cheaper than several jump 1\'s.

Actually, the fuel costs are the same - the fuel required for 1 jump 2 or
two jump-1s is the same (with a jump governor, anyway). So, it\'s only faster
than a series of jump-1s. Presumably, the faster vessels will get more
cargo requests than slower ships.

In my campaign, faster ships COULD charge a premium for faster
deliveries. In fact, small cargo ships wth a high jump capacity could
earn livings as couriers for high priority cargos.

