    'subj' => 'K\'kree, Droyne, Hiver government types',
    'from' => 'Erich Schneider',
    'body' => 'Subject should explain it. These are from Alien Modules 2,5, and 7.

P: (K\'kree) Small station or facility maintained for the good of a
family. Population must be 1 or 2.

Q: (K\'kree) Ruled by a krurruna ("boss", leader of a "herd" of up to
several hundred families) of group of them answerable to an offworld
ghik\'keer!k ("steppelord"). Population must be 3-5.

R: (K\'kree) Ruled by an on-planet ghik\'keer!k or ghir\'ghik\'keer!k
("lord of steppelords"). Population must be 6+.

K\'kree government types are automatic based on population. Ghik\'keer!k
are answerable to a ghir\'ghik\'keer!k, who themselves answer to a
ghir\'k\'reek ("overlord of lords", ruler of multiple planets), who
ultimately are under the Ghik\'keer!k\'ak T\'t\'tkahk Xeng Kirr Tkexirr
("Steppelord of the Two Thousand Worlds" - what a great title!). All
K\'kree rulers (or significant actors in society, for that matter) are
male.

S: (Hiver) "Sept"; council of seven appointed-for-life individuals
which make all decisions relevant to rule of the world; usually give
directives other on-world executive agencies.

T: (Hiver) Unsupervised Anarchy; like type U, but without Federation
observers/advisors.

U: (Hiver) Supervised Anarchy. Virtually no local government, except
for "vigilante committees" rased by nest leaders in response to
urgent social/economic problems. In this case, the Hive Federation
maintains onworld observers/advisors to provide advice to local nest
leaders about potential problems and needs. (Remember, the Hivers
aren\'t greedy and are almost totally pacifistic.)

W: (Hiver) Committee. Government through transitory committees
composed appointed by nest leaders, which disband after producing a
recommendation. Committees try very hard to produce workable solutions
due to the social disgrace accorded recommendations which aren\'t
implemented. (The latter can be the impetus for manipulations, though.)

X: (Droyne) Droyne hierarchy. World government is coordinated by the
Leaders-of-Leaders of oytripin ("communities"), which are themselves
composed of dreskayin (extended families), each headed by a
Leader-of-Leaders. Dreskayin are collections of tyafelmin ("basic
families"), groups of at least six Droyne with one of each caste.
(Gov type 7 Droyne worlds also employ this system, but with multiple
Droyne "nations" instead of a unified system.)

-Erich
