    'index' => 'aa421',
    'topic' => ' Cargo Costs',
    'body' => 'I always assumed that the _net_ listed cargo rates were for last-minute,
_unsecured_ shipments.  The players\' ship not having a reputation, they had
to lay out some of the cargo money for insurance (against their skipping out,
pilfering the load, etc.).  Thus, the 1000 Cr per tonne is what\'s left.

After a while running the same route, and some successful negotiating and use
of Legal skill, they might be able to work out lower premiums (and thus keep
more of the money).  Players being players, however, they usually can\'t stay
out of trouble long enough to build that kind of stable business reputation.

This isn\'t born out in the rules, but I\'m happy with it.  After all, the
economics rules are there for players, not NPCs.  Let the NPCs get the boring
routine cargos -- players should be speculating, smuggling, and cutting deals
to make a somewhat honest credit.
'
