    'topic' => 'solomani questions...',
    'body' => '> Also: apparently, Terra was part of the Imperium from 588 to ?.

    Quite so...

> Why did they join?

    It seemed like a good idea at the time?  Keep in mind that
the entire Solomani Confederation were good Impy subjects for
several centuries...


> What were they before?

    They were the Old Earth Union, or perhaps the Terran
Mercantile Community.  Or whatever they were calling the *OLD*
Terran Confederation (the one that beat the Vilani in the
Interstellar Wars) at that time.


> And why did they seperate?

    Because the Impy policies were very annoying, and because
they could get away with it.  The Imperium never really had the
power to FORCE the Solomani to join/stay in the Imperium, after
all.  The Terrans joined of their own free will, and left when
they were good and ready...


> [Luckily, I _do_ know why they were reconquered in the Solomani
> Rim War of 990 to 1002... to deprive the Solomani racists from
> their rallying flag...]

    Sounds like a large pile of what you find in pastures around
here.  Terra was reconquered as PART of a campaign aimed at the
conquest of the entire so-called Solomani Confederation (more
properly the Solomani Autonomous Region <of the Imperium>).
    Unfortunately (or fortunately, depending on your point of
view), the Imperium did not have the resources to conquer the
Solomani separatists completely.  So after they took Terra (and
exhausted their resources in the doing so), they declared Victory
(Yay!), and went home.  Which was probably lucky for them, since
they still had MOST of the Solomani Confederation left to
conquer, and not nearly enough Fleet or Army to do the
conquering with.  It is likely that the only thing that kept the
the Solomani from continuing the war and reconquering Terra was
that they were entirely too aware of how hard it is to conquer
a world like that, and had no desire to burn themselves out (the
Aslan were still out there on the Borders, after all) trying...

    And then began the Imperial Propaganda Campaign against the
Solomani, which was designed to convince everyone (especially the
racial Solomani outside the COnfederation, and their traditional
allies (like the Darrians, for instance)) that the Solomani
Confederation were EVIL EXPLOITERS of ALL GOOD PEOPLE in the
UNIVERSE...or something like that.  I note that the Terrans plus
the Dolphins plus various uplifted apes make for more diversity
than the predominantly Vilani Imperium, even ignoring the "minor
races" in the Solomani Confederation", which are probably as
numerous (and as poorly treated) as minor races in the Imperium.
   In other words, the "evil Solomani racists" are a figment of
the Impy imagination, just as much as the "evil, mind-burning
Zhodani" are...

                        ----Steve H.
