    'body' => '
Actually, I would like to point something out to those engaged
in debate about the profitability of cargo operations...

There\'s no reason why a regular line is going to have 2 jumps per
month, if you know the ship will be bye on X day, and have a booking
agent on the planet, you can pre-allocate the tonnage to a large
degree, not sit there hunting around for cargos for a week, and jump
out in a few (2 perhaps) days.  Modern containerships spend under
24 hours in port unless something serious is wrong.  A Traveller cargo
ship on a regular route could easily do 3 jumps a month (with over 2 days
on average in port), perhaps 3.5 (with 1 day in port).  That makes just
about anything you can design profitable.

So the core transports, on regular lines etc, are profitable at 1000 Cr/ton.

-george
