Not quite. The information we have about the Terran Mercantile Community
is somewhat contradictory (they took over from the Rule of Man, yet they
were created to circumvent RoM regulations), but I think I\'ve managed to 
reconcile them. The TMC was trade  association formed in -1862 by Terra 
and her closest ex-colonies that later grew into a corporation by the
governments of those worlds.  They took over from whatever Rule of Man
provincial government that used to run that part of the RoM when that
collapsed (in -1690). In -1110 the TMC in turn transformed into the Old 
Earth Union (my interpretation is that they gave up on all worlds outside 
the Union). The Old Earth Union existed from from -1110 to 588 and 
consisted of Terra  and  the  worlds  closest to her:  Barnard,  Calgary,
Dismal,  Ember,  Fenris,  Forlorn,  Hades,  Heiphaistos,  Inferno,
Junction,  Loki,  Midway,  Peraspera,  Prometheus,  Sirius and Ys. After
looking at a map I decided that they would at least have retained a foothold 
in the form of fleet bases on Aggida,  Markhashi, and Meshan too (these 
three worlds are all within jump-3 of Terra  -  and the top technology of
the day ran to jump-3 ships).

