The "Apocryphal":

These are published sectors in which the "canonicality" of the data
is uncertain or questionable.  By topic:

1) Judges Guild.  GDW has revoked the land grant to Judges\' Guild and
   all four sectors they published are "non-canonical".  No loss, folks;
   the quality was bad.  The sectors involved were Ley; Glimmerdrift
   Reaches; Crucis Margin; and Gateway, called "Marantha-Alkahest".
   The retcon was done for _Atlas of the Imperium_.  No information
   from these products appears here.

2) Paranoia Press.  All Paranoia Press materials were judged "non-
   canonical" by GDW at about the same time as all Judges\' Guild
   materials for Traveller were.  They published two sectors, "The
   Beyond" (blue book) and "Vanguard Reaches" (gold book), and
   subsector names for surrounding sectors comes from map margins.
   Both sectors appear on the positional map in DGP\'s canonical
   "Solomani & Aslan", and the star positions do not match. (DGP\'s are,
   IMHO, more interesting.)  Governments were moved around a bit, but
   some of the names are similar (Duchy of Treyln in same place, Esylat
   in subsector B instead of H).  Since something was saved and there
   was some relation to FASA products, the sectors/subsectors they
   listed are below:

