    'body' => '
Casual Encounter/NPC

This is more of an NPC description than a more fleshed out casual encounter,
but I hope it will serve as a springboard to adventures revolving
around the NPC. I\'ve seen NPCs detailed like this in the Casual Encounter
section of Challenge, so that\'s where I took a lot of my cues from.

Any comments or feedback to me would be appreciated.

Having a copy of CT Aliens Module 4, Zhodani, would be handy to help
describe Piebzdhe\'s armor as well as showing you how to say his dang name.

Piebzhde-atl (Captain)
78B8AB Psi-13 32 years old
Guard/Thought Police-O3
Skills:
Cbt Rifleman-2  Grav Vehicle-1
Mechanical-1    NV Communication-3
Forgery-1       Psychology-3
Bribery-1       Streetwise-1
Carousing-1     Interrogation-2

Psi Abilities:
Teleport-13     Telepathy-13
Clairvoyant-13  Special-13 (see below)

Possessions:
(usually) approx Cr.60,000
Gauss Rifle
Snub Pistol
Zhodani-style Chameleon Cbt Armor
(TL13. Guards Model Zhodani armor. everything)
Grav Trunk
 (A Grav Trunk is a large hard-bodied trunk for carrying personal
belongings - like a steamer trunk. It is fitted with low-gain grav
plates on the bottom that allow it to neutralize up to 150kg. It
carries about .5m^3 of cargo, sufficient for his disassembled armor
and rifle. It also has a formidable lock)

Appearance:  Piebzhde is a typical native Zhodani - tall, with dark
hair and complexion.  He is 2.1m tall (6\'10"), 110kg(~240lbs). 
Zhodane\'s gravity is about .85g, so Piebzhde is more comfortable in
slightly lower-gravity areas.  He is, however, used to and
comfortable in fields up to 1.2g. Like most space travelers, he can
withstand up to 2g before becoming severely incapacitated.

His special psionic ability is one which is rare but not unheard of -
perhaps 5% of all non-standard psionic powers are similar to his -
almost perfect memory.  Piebzhde can remember the face and name of
every person he has ever met. He can look at complicated technical
drawings and written scripts he does not even understand and retain
them perfectly, often later transmitting the images telepathically to
someone who can understand them.  To retain very complex images, like
blueprints or text written in a alien language, Piebzhde has to
expend one psi point per day per item memorized that he has not had 
time to study in detail. Detailed study requires 1D+2 hours for
something simple like a document to 1D+2 days for a large building to
1D+2 weeks for an entire spaceport/city.

Background:  Piebzhde is the classic story of Zhodani success - he
was born to a common Zhodani prole family on Zhodane, but because of
his exceptional psionic abilities discovered (relatively) late in life
(14 years) was quickly whisked off to training for life as an
intendant.  He signed on with the Zhodani Consular Guard and was
quickly transferred to the Tavrchedl\' - the Thought Police.

He has served as a shipboard officer, dealing with uncomfortable and
often intemperate troops, helping to weed out dissidents and keep
morale up.  More interestingly, he served as a staff officer on
newly-occupied planets during the Fifth Frontier War, including Lysen
during its occupation in 1109 and later, Querion.  He actively served
in the suppression of local uprisings and the reprogramming of
belligerent Imperials. His exposure to Imperial citizens and his
experience in dealing with non-Zhodani led to his transfer to
Intelligence.  He is quite used to dealing with Imperials, Solomani,
Vargr, Hivers, K\'kree and various other human and alien species.  He
has rarely dealt with Aslan and Aslan client races and will seek to
study them if it can be done safely - otherwise, he will avoid them. 
He avoids traveling in Aslan space.

Description:  Although Piebzhde is his real Zhodani name, he is
rarely know by that name where he is most likely to be found. 
Piebzhde will pick a Vilani or Solomani name as it suits him - often
probing the mind of the person his is dealing with to choose a name
that evokes familiarity or sympathy - the name of a close friend or
relative.  This results in him traveling under dozens of names,
although he is almost never questioned about it.

Piebzhde currently serves as an intelligence officer gathering
intelligence and general information in the Solomani Rim and along
the Solomani/Hiver border.  He is the perfect officer in the perfect
position for what he does - almost all authorities in this area of
space are totally ignorant of psionics and those who aren\'t ignorant
can do very little to stop their use. Piebzhde remembers everything,
everywhere and everyone.  He can forge documents to prove he is anyone
or to get him anywhere, largely aided by his ability to influence the
thoughts of the person checking the documents.  Although no casual
observer would guess that he once served reprogramming the minds of
Imperial citizens on a war border, anyone who works or spends time
with him can detect that he has a military or para-military
background.  His thoroughness and perceptiveness usually makes most
people (semi-mistakenly) think he was once a police officer in the
Solomani/Imperial sense - one who solves mysteries, tracks down
criminals and enforces the law.  While he will deny any accusations of
being a police officer, he will play up to anyone who suspects him of
such - he will make dramatic Sherlock Holmes-like inspections of crime
or archaeological scenes and conduct  Hercules Poirot-esque group
interrogations given the chance.  Since he can, of course, read minds
and see though walls, these are more showmanship than actual wit.  In
general, aside from these rare demonstrations, he is very cautious
about the use of his psionic powers although his prolonged stay in
Solomani space has made him less cautious than he should be. He does,
however, resist the temptation to reprogram disturbed individuals
he meets in Solmani space.  This is not to say he has never done it.
It is usually a bad idea, as he can leave a person effectively lobotomized.

His only major problem is the difficulty in returning him to Zhodani
space to give the occasional report - he is well known in the Marches
from his military police activities during the Fifth frontier war. 
Even worse, the closer he gets to Zhodani space, the more likely he
is to be recognized by Imperial authorities either as a Zhodani, or
worse, as himself.  Due the his unfamiliarity with Aslan customs and
minds, coupled with the large areas of empty space between the
Consulate and Aslan space, he is forced to go through the familiar
but unfriendly territory of the Spinward Marches whenever he wants to
return to Zhodani space.  This can pose a considerable problem.

Adventure Possibilities:  1) If the campaign is taking place in the
early/mid fifth frontier war (1108-1110), Piebzhde may be encountered
as a military police officer commanding a garrison on Lysen or
Querion. In this case, the players will meet him as a police officer
who may be their friend or foe.

2) If the campaign is later, around 1112, he will be somewhere around
the Solomani Rim, towards the Hiver federation border.  He will be
actively gathering intelligence on Solomani activity, Hiver
technology, possible Ancient sites and general cultural information.

