    'body' => 'Rob Miracle wrote
>I don\'t know if GDW has ever defined the effects of [jump] space, so make
>it up.
For those who may not want to make it up, I quote from Starship Operator\'s
Manual, by Digest Group Publications, at 11-12:
"In order for a starship to be able to travel through jumpspace, the ship\'s
jump drive must first open a portal into the desired jumpspace.  To
accomplish this feat, the drive energizes a lanthanum grid which has been
incorporated into the ship\'s hull.  The vast energy flow across this hull
grid net causes \'unravelling\' to begin in the region of space the ship
occupies.  As the discharge of the drive energies to the hull grid
increases, the unravelling becomes great enough to open up a \'rift\' in the
weave of jumpspace. 
* * *
"As the rift closes, the protective jump field \'bubble\' around the ship is
also sealed.  This bubble keeps out the strange physics of jumpspace, and
serves to provide a safe region for the ship, where the normal physics of
our universe operate.  The bubble follows the contour of the jump grid
exactly, and appears as a dull, gray, undulating \'wall\' about a meter from
the surface of the hull."

--Glenn
