Unfortunately, according to the Zhodani word generation tables, the
cluster "zdh" is impossible. Which leads to...

>If it is spelled Piebzhde, then it would be pronounced as the above
>but with a drunken slur: "pyebzh-deh," with the \'zh\' being pronounced
>like the \'s\' in \'measure\' or the \'z\' in \'azure\' (admittedly, some regional
>English speakers pronounce both of these as a bare \'z\'), or in the
>same way that I was taught to pronounce (many years ago...) the French
