Maybe you could say it this way if you want an Anglic
accent. According to the tables, again, "zhd" (as well as "cht",
"sht", and "jd") are considered unbreakable consonant cluster by the
Zhodani. I thus think the syllabification is "pieb-zhde". One just has
to learn how to pronounce (and think of) things like "zhd" as single
consonants. Since I\'ve been looking at a lot of sector maps and other
Zhodani stuff lately, I have been walking around muttering things like
"Tiens-pev-nekr", "Echt-ovr Da-zhia", "Vlez-pridl-iashav", "Tavr-chedle\'",
and "Zhdant" under my breath, so I\'m beginning to see things this way.
(With the help of my psionic tutor, of course....)

Personally, I think it\'s likely the race calls themselves "Zhdani" -
natural if their homeworld is "Zhdant" - and the "o" gets stuck in by 
tounge-tied Imperials (especially Vilani native speakers, who can\'t
handle the vast majority of consonant clusters; but then, Vilani has
no "o", so they probably say "Shadani" with the first "a" a schwa).

I wonder who first called the Vilani homeworld "Vland"? Certainly not
speakers of High Vilani, who probably call it "Bilanid".

I also wonder if the GDW folks have generation tables for Vegan names
somewhere. (I was reading something about Hong Kong the other day and
