a Solomani trait is that the Solomani would eventually pass the
Vilani and leave them in the dust, so to speak.  Since the default
aging is given for Solomani or Solomani/Vilani descent, this may
even make sense.  There would still be pure-breed Vilani, of
course, but the Solomani numbers would eventually be higher, and
the Solomani-Vilani mixes would tend more towards Solomani.

> Or are you making the 
> (idiotic) assumption that the Solomani birthrate will be high
> long enough to match the Vilani numbers, then will taper off to
> ZPG?  If so, reread my first two lines of this post (the rude ones).

Of course, genetics are not so simple, so that is possible (though
unlikely).  It is also possible that high birthrate is merely a
BEHAVIORAL trait (which I was trying to point out all along), in
which case anything is possible.

However, it is unreasonable to assume that the Vilani maintain a
zero population growth.  As you pointed out, they could never
recover from disasters that way.

Overall, I think I prefer the concept of some large-scale
disasters, coupled with a somewhat higher Solomani birth rate,
which perhaps could be attributed to a "colonize and populate"
attitude as opposed to a "status quo" attitude.

-Jerry

