Not having Cats & Rats with me, I can\'t check this, but I seem to remember
that the Solomani used various sorts of artificial means to increase their
population during the Nth Interstellar Wars.  The implication was that they
used In Vitro fertilization of human ova, froze \'em, and then used...I
dunno, Birth Labs or some-such to grow a bunch of kids really quickly.

This sort of thing would be pretty far beyond the Vilani\'s pitiful medical
technology and would allow the Terrans to populate colony worlds pretty fast
(although trying to raise all the kids with only a handful of colonists
might have been awfully tricky -- I\'m not sure how such societies would
develop, but they\'d be fairly interesting...)

Can anybody verify this, or am I misremembering?

