JSHiggin: 
In a piece of mail in the XBOAT digest 123, I noted you talking about the 
\'huge\' Solomani population to Rimward...  Here\'s the latest (well, I note 
that no one else knows about it....! so it must be the latest - even if 
my HIWG stuff was written 2 years ago plus)

Back in the good ol days of HIWG - I am not familirar with it now,., I 
did an article on the Solomani population to rimward of the Solomai Rim 
sector...

Basically I based the discussion on a section of text out of one of the 
LIbrary entries about the proportion of population compared with 
Vilani....  I then counted the total number of HiPop worlds in the 
Imperium (out of the Atlas) and came up with a total High POP worlds that 
must exist in the Solomani sphere.  I then back tracked to work out how 
many must be off the map in the Atlas.

The density of HiPop worlds was equal to or in excess of the density 
present in the Solomani Rim sector!!!! 

If you have a copy of the Atlas handy take a look at that one page....  
The number of worlds named (Hi Pop) is _IMMENSE_...  To realise that the 
rest or the Solomani sphere, to rimward of that covered by the Atlas (3 
sectors centred on Solomani Rim), is this dense in all of the three other 
sectors is mind boggling to me!!

It has several times encouraged me to make a \'large scale strategic\' game 
using this fact and seeing how the total industrial output of the 
Solomani - in such a small region of space (6 sectors is small cf Vilani 
25+).  Interesting results...I\'d say that the Solomani could easily 
attack and occupy, controlling, upto two or three sectors into the 3rd 
Imperium.

If you get the chance look up a document index on the Solomani articles 
with HIWG.  You should find mine in there somewhere - surname BOOL, don\'t 
remember my membership number.

Anyway...happy hunting...back to work!

//count@easynet.co.uk
