    'body' => '
The interesting thing about fashions in the Imperium, as well as music 
and other cultural traits is the time lag in communications. A fashion 
would appear in one area and begin propagating at the speed of jump. Very 
\'hot\' or highly promoted material would be spread faster than a less-well 
publicized fashion would. 
	This raises two issues, context and mutation. Two ideas which 
arise in the same place and time would not neccessarily be communicated 
at the same rate. So culture would be out of touch with continuity, in 
fact causality in a sociological sense would break down.
	Further complicating the issue is retransmision. If a wave of 
fashion is altered by a subculture before being passed along the lines of 
communication then culture becomes more heterogeneous as the distance 
from cultural centers increases.
	As a sociological study, the 3rd Imperium is fascinating.

Michael Carter Llaneza
Conceptual Design Services             The Worse it gets,
Pi Kappa Phi                           The more I get used to it.
"I am the NRA"			       Duty Now For The Future

