Scenario - Kyeth
================

Contract
----

A contract is offered by Molke Heavy Industries to investigate the
fate of a research expedition into the Davion subsector. The mission
of the lost expedition was to explore the subsector for trade
opportunities. A 400 ton frontier trader may be assigned to the group
for the mission. They are to depart from Raphia and retrace the flight
plan of the expedition. 

Background
----

The expedition consisted of 7 ships. A type T patrol cruiser 
acted as the command ship. Three Enhanced Performance Scouts
were used to survey unexplored systems in advance of the main
expedition. Three Close Escorts provided protection for the
expedition.
The expedition commander was Jotarin Ramik, a young merchant captain
who had recently successfully opened trade with the systems of Kubae 
and Jascek. He built his reputation as a 2nd officer on a frontier
trader buying empty cargo from the owner and speculating on small
cargos. His rapid rise has earned him some enemies in the trader
community. He is known as an eccentric captain; one who actually
enjoys low berth travel. He has spent a lot of time researching
improved low berths.

Jotarin Ramik 878BA9, Age 34, Merchant, 4 terms.  Final Rank - .
Assets: MCr9.2 (personal wealth),
Equipment Qualified On:
Starship, Ship\'s Guns, Vacc Suit
Skills:  Broker-3, Liason-2, Leader-1, Vacc-1, Pilot-1, Gunnery-1,
Handgun-1

Comments: Jotar owes his success to the fact that he has strong
psionic abilities. He has been careful to hide this fact and uses it
to his advantage in trade negotiations. He has found that while in
low passage his psionic powers remain available to him if he is in a
customized chill berth (as opposed to a low berth). He frequently
travels in this manner, putting his first officer in charge of all
shipboard duties. Because of this longtime associates have noticed a
slowing of the aging process in the last five years.

(Referee Only - Jotarin\'s psionic ability is beyond normal telepathy.
He constantly intercepts thoughts of those around him. Play him as 
if he were overhearing the players\' discussion around the gaming table.)

Frontier Trader
Forerunner  FT-4234851-000000-50004-0    MCr 201.7      400 tons
    batteries bearing         1   1	     Crew = 4
    batteries                 1   1	     TL = 14 (PP is TL 15)
Pass = 4. Low = 0. Craft = gig. Cargo = 71. Fuel = 144. EP = 32. Agility = 4.

Gig         GG-0106B21-000000-20000-0    MCr 27.65      20 tons
    batteries bearing         1    	     Crew = 1
    batteries                 1    	     TL = 14 (PP is TL 15)
Pass = 7. Emergency Low = 3. Cargo = 2. Fuel = 2.2. EP = 2.2. 


Valkek 
----

At Valkek, it is learned that the MT has put a contract out on the
destruction of the players vessel. 1 MCr is offered for conclusive
evidence that the recovery mission was destroyed. 

Scarab
----

At Scarab, the astrographic archives of the Scorpi Aureak Advanced
Research Directorate (SAARD) will be made available. This will
give the players accurate data for all systems up to the edge of 
explored space. In exchange, Molke Industries has agreed to let 
SAARD analyze all ships logs recovered from expedition vessels. 


Quorus
----

In a Quorus starport bar, the recovery team is offered a substantial
bribe to drop their current contract and make a special freight haul
to Rulmela.  The agent making the offer may be recognized as the
pirate Drakob Khovar by players with streetwise experience. If they
accept the cargo, Cr200,000 will be advanced to them. Another
Cr800,000 will await them upon delivery.


Rumela
----

At Rumela, the special freight reciever will not come to the arranged
meeting in the starport. Investigation of the cargo will reveal drums
of liquid chemical byproducts. Some have begun leaking. The freight
haul is an obvious set-up. The local authorities have been informed
and are sealing off this wing of the starport. A Type T Patrol cruiser 
is maneuvering to block escape off-world. The leaking chemicals are 
beginning to strain the environmental systems. 
 
(In Classic Traveller tradition, further events are to be determined
by the referee.)

If the cargo was not accepted, a 400 ton Corsair will be waiting to 
ambush the recovery team as they enter the system.


Draask
----

At Draask, a transponder signal from an expedition Close Escort will
be detected originating from the planet\'s surface. Four survivors from
the crew are found living in near starvation conditions. They will
tell of a corsair attack by five 400 ton raiders. Their ship was
crippled and forced down on the planet. The remainder of the
expedition drew off the attackers and jumped. The expedition was to
pick them up on their return trip. They are non-technical specialists
and are incapable of repairing their ship.

The foilage present on the planet contains an incompatible amino
acid which makes most food poisonous to the crew. They have survived
for three months on the rations of the ship and by making use of the
emergency low berths in the gig. They will agree to low berth passage
for the duration of the recovery team\'s mission if required. 

A civilization of small reptilian humanoids inhabits Draask. They
possess TL-4 technology and are ruled by a tribal system. Their 
religion is based on the worship of Agralthg, god of the three-lobed eye.
Apparently, at irregular intervals a large body is seen in the sky,
resembling a winged three-lobed eye. It remains for a month with its
wings spread before it disappears. The population spends this time in 
worship and feasting. Recently, Agralthg\'s visit resulted in severe
disruption among psionic Draask. This is due to hostility caused by the 
radio signal (see below). If the Draask capture expedition members,
they will attempt to placate their god by sacrificing the humans.


Pnakus
----

At Pnakus, an Enhanced Performance Scout from the expedition is found
abandonded in orbit around a habitable planet. The pilot, Maxmillian
Vismark, was marooned on the planet when the life support systems
failed in his ship. 

Maxmillian Vismark 777A87, Age 34, Ex-scout, four terms, Enlisted in
Communications. 60,000 Cr 
Special Assignments: Special Mission - courier.
Awards and Decorations: XP = 9. Morale = 12.
Equipment Qualified On: Electronics, Starship, Ship\'s weapons, Rifle,
Handgun, Vacc Suit
Skills: Gunnery-3, Broker-2, Navig-2, Handgun-2, Pilot-1, Brawling-1,
Electronics-1, Vacc-1, Prospecting-1

Maxmillian Vismark was recently discharged from the Rhalta Scout
Service. He was hired for the expedition because of his familiarity
with Enhanced Performance Scouts. When rescued, he will tell what he
knows of the fate of the expedition. He had finished exploring hex
0436 when he jumped to 0326 Kyeth. He found the expedition in close
proximity to several large vessels. When he signaled by radio,
several of the vessels accelerated to meet him. Severe electrical
discharges were exchanged from the vessels to his ship causing
computer failure. When he brought the computer online and began to
maneuver his vessel the attack resumed. He tried to jump out of the
system when a misjump occurred. He found himself at Pnakus with a
severely damaged ship. He travelled to the surface of a habitable
planet and has survived there for two months. His scout ship has
suffered computer, power plant, and life support damage. 

Maxmillian suspects that Jotar has made some special agreement with
a newly contacted alien race and wishes to keep others from learning
this. He will graciously agree to join the recovery expedition in
any role which is useful.


Kyeth
----

At Kyeth, the recovery team finds 18 alien vessels clustered around the
surviving ships of the expedition. The expedition will attempt to 
signal by maser that radio transmissions should not be used. If 
radio transmission occurs, the aliens may interpret this as a
challange. The survivors are still repairing their ships although 
two are jump worthy now. If radio is not used, the recovery team 
will be permitted to approach the expedition and board. The 
survivors will relate the experiences which have occurred at Kyeth.

When the expedition intially entered the system, twenty vessels of 
about 1000 tons each reacted agressively. A universal hail 
transmission provoked an attack. Electromagnetic pulses from the 
aggressors wreaked havok among the expedition ships. On the bridge 
of the Darkind , Jotar was critically injured. As the expedition ships 
evaded the attack, the second officer managed to get Jotar to his 
chill berth. While in his dream state, Jotar was able to psionically 
contact the Kyeth and convince them to end the attack. He was able 
to determine that the attacking vessels were not ships crewed by aliens
but lifeforms. Jotarin named them Kyeth for the system in which they
were discovered, but he suspects they originated elsewhere.

The next six weeks were spent repairing the ships and preparing to 
depart. A week ago, Jotar arranged for a 20 ton gig to be equipped 
with his chill berth and the maximum cargo of provisions it could 
carry. He departed the Darkind and flew into the maw of the largest 
Kyeth present. He left behind records promoting his first officer to 
captain and explaining his mission. He had learned that the Kyeth 
were capable of interstellar travel and wished to explore the Khalij 
Expanse from within one of the beings. A day later, the largest 
Kyeth moved away from the rest and disappeared from normal space at
a phenomenal speed.


The Kyeth
----

The Kyeth are massive vaccuum dwelling life forms discovered in the
Kyeth system from which they are named. They are intelligent and 
highly psionic. The young develop in the atmosphere of a large gas 
giant. Their immature form is a tubular structure composed of several
gasbag subdivisions. During this stage they resemble airships and
drift with the atmospheric winds. They can change altitude by
absorbing or rejecting heat which expands or contracts the gasbags.
Their metabolism processes the gases present in the atmosphere.
Gradually, the soft membranes harden and form a thick polymeric
shell. As their mass increases, a psionic telekenesis ability 
develops to keep them continually aloft. The mature Kyeth leaves the
atmosphere and lives in space. A very efficient absorption of stellar
radiation supplies their energy needs.

The adult Kyeth has a trilobed symmetrical pod structure. Three 
large fans can be unfolded for the purpose of absorbing or 
transmitting energy. Three long appendages exist slightly forward of
the fans. Further forward, the three lobes separate to form a maw 
when opened. Small asteroids can be injested through this opening 
when minerals are required. When the fans are folded, they lie next 
to the tail and aid in psionic movement. In the center of the body 
are internal organs. Running down the center is the system capable of
breaking down minerals for the purpose of regeneration and growth. 
The brain is a ring shaped organ towards the front. Behind it is the 
energy storage organ which acts as a bank of capacitors. At the rear 
is the reproductive organ which stores jelly like embryos for 
release in gas giant atmospheres. 

In addition to their antigrav lift, Kyeth are capable of high power
electromagnetic pulse, which can be used as a weapon. The fans focus 
the bursts, which inficts damage as a particle accelerator of equal 
EP output. The output can be up to one fourth the total charge. 

Kyeth are capable of limited interstellar travel through a psionic 
teleportation effect which approaches stutterwarp when rapidly cycled.
Each hop requires an instant of thought to resolve the destination. 
Within a gravity field this resolution is difficult so very short hops
are used. In the emptiness of interstellar space they are capable of 
FTL travel as the lengths of the hops increases.

The Kyeth communicate by radio emissions. They can also communicate 
telepathically, though less efficiently. They have little interest in
human ships except when radio transmissions excite them to attack. 
Meson and Ladar transmissions are not received by the Kyeth and have 
no effect. Active sensors may distress them. They exhibit above animal
intelligence, barely sapient.

The Kyeth can be up to 18000 tons (3D6*1000) in displacement. The 
energy storage is equal to 1 EP per 25 ton of total displacement. They
can achieve 1-G acceleration through antigrav. One month is required 
to fully charge the capacitors in most systems.

When first encountered most will have their fans extended, basking in
the stellar radiation. A few will be navigating the asteroid fields in
search of minerals.

There is evidence that the Kyeth did not evolve naturally. The home
system of this alien race is not known. They have been encountered 
throughout the Khalij Expanse. It is surmised by some researchers that
Kyeth were developed by another alien race for space travel. Remains
found in the Yekt system (0433) are of a large Kyeth fitted with
hardware which would be weapons systems and propulsion rockets. 



NPC\'s
----
Drakob Khovar 878BA9, Age 50, Pirate, 7 terms.  Final Rank - Leader.
Assets: MCr429 (personal wealth),  Command of Tarjak pirate network
(unlimited for campaign purposes)
Equipment Qualified On:
Starship, Ship\'s Guns, Vacc Suit, Laser Rifle, Cutlass 
Skills:  Leader-3, Laser-2, Tactics-2, Ship\'s Tactics-2, Gambling-
2, Streetwise-1, Forgery-1, Cutlass-1, Vacc-1, Pilot-1, Gunnery-1

Comments: After growing up in the ghettos of Metris, Drakob Khovar
joined the Tuarak Privateers.  His career advanced rapidly due to his
cunning and ruthlessness.  He commands over 40 corsair vessels.  He 
is wanted by the Rhalta Domain and the Alaetra Sovereignty for crimes
ranging from fraud to piracy and murder.  In appearance he is a small
unattractive man, but his charisma inspires the loyalty of those who 
serve under him.  
