    'body' => 'Regards my earlier mail on the Sol pop, and some return messages...

The information on the Solomani population was in both MT and CT library 
_I think_.  However I am away from my stuff (gibber gibber wimper - 
withdrawl symptoms) so I can\'t check for you sorry (Im on the other side 
of the world...)

Also as for raising the average population of worlds - I used averages!  
To expand, if my memory serves me correctly (HIWG 208.01 may give more 
info on method), I took the proportion of Hi Pop to Low Pop worlds from 
Solomani Rim, and worked out the average pop of the lower pop, unnamed, 
worlds and of the high pop, named, worlds

This gave a low pop or 10^4 odd and a high pop avg between 10^9 and 
10^10.  As the difference is x10^5, most of the pop appeared in hi pop 
worlds.  Considering the way the Solomani colonised worlds to rimward - 
baby banks and genetics - I would have thought they would find most 
suitable \'garden\' worlds and boosted pop through the roof there, while kept 
pops in other \'resource\' worlds to the optimal for resource recovery.

If you raise the pop of all of the worlds then you end up with every 
world having a pop close to 1 bill if not more (ie all having major 
populations, ie named worlds.  This is due to the fact that for every 
world having (let\'s say) 90 billion - if you reduced the number to 10 
billion, you could raise the pop of 80 worlds to major world status!!!!!
(1 bill+)

Hmmm scary thought playing with numbers of people that way!!!!  Also 
scarier if you consider the tax potential under Striker and TCS that 
